/* ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
   EDITORIAL THEMES — six COMPLETE palettes (theme-completion ship)
   Replaces base.css lines 383-488. Each block now overrides EVERY live
   theme-dependent token (31 lines), not just the original 11 — closing the
   mixed-palette bugs (frozen --cb-mute-2, frozen --cb-brass-rgb tints, etc.).

   Provenance:
   · 11 palette anchors per theme — verified, unchanged from base.css v8.24.x
     (except --cb-mute: AA-safe values from the verified contrast table in
     .claude/state/design-audit-2026-06-08/SYSTEMIC-mute-ramp-aa.md, >=4.6:1
     on each theme's canvas; taste-adjacent — Founder staging review required).
   · Derived ramp tokens — computed from the clubhouse :root ratios
     (ink-2/-soft = ink+0.46/0.70 toward charcoal; mute-2/-3 = mute+0.56/0.84
     toward chalk-3; mute-faint = avg(mute-2,mute-3); mute-1 = mute x0.94;
     brass-2/-3/-deep/ink-link = brass x1.13/x1.30/x0.76/x0.50; green-3 =
     green x(1.92,1.69,1.35); felt = green-2 x0.85; green-ink tuple = green
     x0.65). Pending the per-theme vision pass (P2/V1) before prod.

