# Settings Theme Picker — implementation spec (Ship: theme-picker, follows theme-css commit)

## Files
1. `src/pages/settings.js` — replace the DISPLAY placeholder (L111-143: the "full theme picker arrives in an upcoming update" row + the stale `_themePreviews` array + `.set-swatches` render). Keep the Sunlight toggle (L144-149) below the picker.
2. `src/core/theme.js` — two small patches so the picker coexists with Sunlight mode (see §Sunlight).
3. `src/styles/components.css` — add the `.theme-row` family (token-driven, no hardcoded colors except swatch data).

## Data flow (existing API, no new schema)
```js
var _unlocked = (currentProfile && currentProfile.unlockedThemes) || []; // 0d-ii grant flow writes this later; [] is safe today
var _themes = getAvailableThemes(_unlocked);   // theme.js:69 — already sorts by order + hides hidden_until_unlocked locked themes
var _activeId = document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-palette-theme') || getCurrentTheme(); // palette attr wins while sunlight is on
```
Result for a typical member today: clubhouse, twilight_links, linen_draft (selectable) + bourbon_room (visible, locked — `hidden_until_unlocked:false`). champion_sunday / course_record appear only once unlocked. This is existing registry behavior — do not special-case.

## Swatch data (single source, mirrors base.css [data-theme] blocks EXACTLY)
```js
// Swatch hexes are data — a literal preview of each theme's palette,
// permitted like Visual Reference hole-dots. MUST match base.css theme blocks.
var THEME_SWATCHES = {
  clubhouse:       { canvas: "#E7E0CD", green: "#2F4A3A", brass: "#B4893E" },
  twilight_links:  { canvas: "#DACFB6", green: "#1A2A3E", brass: "#C48540" },
  linen_draft:     { canvas: "#E8DEC5", green: "#2B3A2E", brass: "#B8743A" },
  champion_sunday: { canvas: "#E0D3B7", green: "#4A1D24", brass: "#C68A3C" },
  bourbon_room:    { canvas: "#DCCAA4", green: "#3D2817", brass: "#B8743A" },
  course_record:   { canvas: "#E3D8BD", green: "#0C2A22", brass: "#8A8572" }
};
```
This deletes the stale `_themePreviews` array (its twilight accent #d4a857 was the retired legacy gold; clubhouse accent #c89a4b never matched brass — audit item resolved here).

## Markup (one row per theme, inside the Display section card)
Container: `<div class="theme-picker" role="radiogroup" aria-label="Theme">` preceded by a `.set-row` header — label "Theme", desc (exact copy): **"Six editorial themes. Three ready today, three to earn. Your pick follows you to any device you sign into."**

Each unlocked theme:
```html
<button type="button" class="theme-row" role="radio" aria-checked="true|false"
        data-theme-id="twilight_links" onclick="settingsPickTheme('twilight_links')">
  <span class="theme-row__chip" aria-hidden="true" style="background:#DACFB6">
    <span class="theme-row__band" style="background:#1A2A3E"></span>
    <span class="theme-row__dot" style="background:#C48540"></span>
  </span>
  <span class="theme-row__main">
    <span class="theme-row__name">Twilight Links</span>
    <span class="theme-row__desc">Dusk over the coastal course. Cool air, warm brass.</span>
  </span>
  <span class="theme-row__check"><!-- 16px SVG check, visible only when active --></span>
</button>
```
Locked theme: same row + `theme-row--locked`, `aria-disabled="true"`, check slot renders a 14px SVG padlock in `var(--cb-mute)`, onclick → `settingsThemeLockedHint(id)`. Row stays at FULL structure (no opacity-0.5 ghosting like the old swatches); only the chip gets `filter:saturate(.55)`. P10: a locked row always answers what/where/action via its hint toast — no dead taps.

Row descs (exact copy, Caddy voice):
- Clubhouse — "The house default. Quiet confidence, tournament program."
- Twilight Links — "Dusk over the coastal course. Cool air, warm brass."
- Linen Draft — "Bright morning light, reading chair by the window."
- Champion Sunday — "Burgundy worn after a win."
- Bourbon Room — "The lodge after the round. Earned with tenure."
- Course Record — "Ledger paper and silver brass. The rarest."

## CSS (components.css — token-driven)
```css
.theme-picker{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:var(--sp-2);margin-top:var(--sp-3)}
.theme-row{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:var(--sp-3);width:100%;min-height:56px; /* 44pt+ */
  padding:var(--sp-2) var(--sp-3);background:var(--surface-raised);border:1px solid var(--border-subtle);
  border-radius:var(--radius-lg);text-align:left;transition:border-color var(--dur-quick) var(--ease-standard)}
.theme-row[aria-checked="true"]{border-color:var(--cb-brass);box-shadow:0 0 0 1px var(--cb-brass)}
.theme-row__chip{position:relative;width:40px;height:40px;border-radius:var(--radius-md);overflow:hidden;
  border:1px solid var(--border-default);flex-shrink:0}
.theme-row__band{position:absolute;left:0;right:0;bottom:0;height:14px}
.theme-row__dot{position:absolute;top:5px;right:5px;width:10px;height:10px;border-radius:50%}
.theme-row__name{display:block;font-weight:600;font-size:var(--text-md);color:var(--text-primary)}
.theme-row__desc{display:block;font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--cb-mute);margin-top:2px}
.theme-row__check{margin-left:auto;color:var(--cb-brass);flex-shrink:0}
.theme-row--locked .theme-row__chip{filter:saturate(.55)}
.theme-row--locked .theme-row__name{color:var(--cb-mute)}
```
Keyboard/a11y: native buttons (focusable, Enter/Space) + the global :focus-visible brass ring. radiogroup/radio + aria-checked gives screen readers the selection model.

## Handlers (settings.js)
```js
function settingsPickTheme(id) {
  var html = document.documentElement;
  var current = html.getAttribute('data-palette-theme') || (typeof getCurrentTheme === 'function' ? getCurrentTheme() : 'clubhouse');
  if (id === current) return;
  saveThemeChoice(id).then(function () {
    if (Router.toast) Router.toast(_THEME_TOASTS[id] || ('Theme set — ' + id));
  }).catch(function () {
    // Theme already applied locally + localStorage by applyTheme(); only the Firestore write failed.
    if (Router.toast) Router.toast("Theme set on this device — couldn't reach the clubhouse to save it everywhere. It'll sync next time you're online.");
  });
  // In-place update — no Router.go full re-render (avoids the resize-flash class of bug):
  document.querySelectorAll('.theme-row[role="radio"]').forEach(function (el) {
    el.setAttribute('aria-checked', el.getAttribute('data-theme-id') === id ? 'true' : 'false');
  });
  // swap the check icon visibility per aria-checked via CSS sibling rule or small DOM pass
}
function settingsThemeLockedHint(id) {
  if (Router.toast) Router.toast(_THEME_LOCK_HINTS[id] || 'This one is earned, not picked. Keep teeing it up.');
}
```
Apply is INSTANT: `saveThemeChoice` (theme.js:158) runs `applyTheme` synchronously before the Firestore promise — the whole app re-themes on tap.

Toast copy (exact, Caddy voice):
```js
var _THEME_TOASTS = {
  clubhouse:       "Back to the Clubhouse. Never a bad call.",
  twilight_links:  "Twilight Links. Last group out, lights coming on.",
  linen_draft:     "Linen Draft. Crisp as a morning tee time.",
  champion_sunday: "Champion Sunday. You earned the burgundy.",
  bourbon_room:    "Bourbon Room. Pull up a chair by the fire.",
  course_record:   "Course Record. The rarest page in the ledger."
};
var _THEME_LOCK_HINTS = {
  bourbon_room:    "Bourbon Room pours for members with tenure. Keep showing up — it unlocks with time in the league.",
  champion_sunday: "Champion Sunday is worn after a win. Take down an event and it's yours.",
  course_record:   "Course Record opens for record-setters. Go put your name in the book."
};
```

## Sunlight coexistence (theme.js patches — required, currently desyncs)
Today `toggleSunlightMode` (settings.js:488) stashes the palette in `data-palette-theme` and sets `data-theme="sunlight"`. If the picker called `applyTheme` while sunlight is on, it would stomp `data-theme` and silently kill sunlight while `pb_sunlight=1` persists. Patch theme.js:
1. `applyTheme` (L55): if `document.documentElement.getAttribute('data-theme') === 'sunlight'`, write the new id to `data-palette-theme` instead of `data-theme` (localStorage + Firestore writes unchanged).
2. `getCurrentTheme` (L64): read `data-palette-theme` first, then `data-theme`.
When sunlight is ON, render one `.set-note set-note--mute` line under the picker (P10 explicit state): **"Sunlight mode is on — your theme is saved and shows the moment you switch Sunlight off."**

## Edge cases
- Logged-out/no-db: `saveThemeChoice` resolves immediately after local apply — picker still works, toast fires.
- `currentProfile.unlockedThemes` missing → `[]` (all unlock themes locked/hidden per registry flags).
- Defensive: `settingsPickTheme` on a locked id — `saveThemeChoice` validates against THEMES, but also guard in the handler (`if (row has theme-row--locked) return settingsThemeLockedHint(id)`).
- No Firestore rules change needed: `members/{uid}.theme` is already written by saveThemeChoice today (self-doc update path) — no AMD-018 gate touched.

## QA gate (per parbaughs-ship-cycle)
1. E2E (tests/e2e/flows/): pick each default theme → assert `documentElement[data-theme]`, `localStorage.pb_theme`, Firestore member doc `.theme`; reload persists; locked row tap leaves attribute unchanged + toast visible; sunlight ON + pick → `data-palette-theme` updated, `data-theme` stays "sunlight".
2. V1 vision: capture Settings + Home + Profile in all 6 themes (3 viewports), Read PNGs, verify swatch chip matches the applied surface.
3. Hook 5: version bump in utils.js + package.json; bump `CACHE_NAME` in public/sw.js (manual step).
4. Caddy Notes entry (member-visible feature): "Theme picker is open — six editorial looks, three ready now, three to earn. Settings → Display."
